==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Promulgate
<hw>Pro*mul"gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Promulgated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Promulgating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>promulgatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>promulgare</ets> to promulgate; of
unknown origin. Cf. <er>Promulge</er>.]</ety> <def>To make known by open
declaration, as laws, decrees, or tidings; to publish; <as>as, to
<ex>promulgate</ex> the secrets of a council</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To publish; declare; proclaim. See
<er>Announce</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Promulgation</ent>⟦br⟧
